  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Re:Increasing Citizens participation and inclusive governance for improved Water, Sanitation and Hyg</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The concept of social accountability is beginning to yield results and deserves to be sustained in 2018. Although there are still several areas and grounds to cover as the budgetary allocation in the areas of water provision by the state government were poorly implemented.  However with sustain efforts and engagement with the duty bearers by the communities in which JDPC would be providing the technical supports, more gains would be derived from social accountability hence the need for social accountability 2018. There would therefore be need to engage more with the legislators who make appropriations, approve budget and carry out oversight functions for effective implementation of the budget for the good of the people.

JDPC will therefore work with the already mobilized citizens/communities to dialogue with the duty bearers to further the demand for improved supply of water to the people of Kogi State, create awareness and advocate for behavioural change on sanitary and hygiene practices in Kogi State.

JDPC will sustain her steering committee membership to accommodate more willing and passionate like minds that will plan the schedules and execute the activities of the project (follow-up/ advocacy visits to Ministries, Departments and Agencies (MDAs, accountability town hall meetings for representatives and other government officials, Radio programmes and sensitization/capacity building visits to the communities so as to strengthen the capacities of the existing community development  structures for effectiveness in preparing and presenting community charter of demands to person seeking their votes. Community development associations like Obagede development Association has become more formidable and are now engaging their local government authorities to demand for improve service delivery. Felele and Kabawa communities are becoming more formidable as well. There would therefore be need to give a little more push to the community development associations.</narrative>
  </description>
